Variables:

    - variables are used to store the data.

    - in general we will declare the variables in javascript by using "var" keyword.

    - By using variables we can store  all categories of data

    Ex.
        integer data.
        string data.
        float data.
        objects

            --
            --
            --

     //Storing the string data
     var data = "Welcome to JavaScript !";

    //Storing the integer data
    var data = 100;

    //Storing the float data
     var data = 100.1;

    //Storing the objects
     var data = new my_obj();

    //Storing the JSON objects
     var data = {'name_one':'bharat','name_two':'vinay','name_three':'mono'};


 display the data on browser console:
 ------------------------------------
 console.log("Welcome to JavaScript !");


 display the data on webpage(html page)
 --------------------------------------
 document.write("Welcome to JavaScript !");


 Getting the References of HTML Elements to JavaScript:
 ------------------------------------------------------
 <h1 id="first_h1"></h1>
 <h1 id="second_h1"></h1>
 <h1 id="third_h1"></h1>


 document.getElementById("first_h1").innerHTML = "Data From MySQL DB Soon...!";

 document.getElementById("second_h1").innerHTML="Data from Mango DB soon";

 document .getElementById("third_h1").innerHTML = "Data from Cassandra DB soon..!";


 - we can include the javascript into webpage by using "<script></script>" tag.

 Ex.

    <script type="text/javascript">

        //Business Logic.

    </script>


 - we have two types of variables.

       1. global variables

       2. local variables

1. Global variables are available to application scope.
    Ex.4
        <script type="text/javascript">
            var data = "Data From DN Soon....";
            var name="hello";

            if(name=="hello"){
                console.log(data);
                var var_one = "i am local variable";
                console.log(var_one);
            }

            console.log(var_one);

        </script>

2. local variables are available perticular block in application.










